{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, for the inputs Q, K, and V, the weight vectors are calculated as:Attention (Q, K, V) = softmax ( QK T √ d k) V.(2)The dimension of the query and key is denoted by d k. The attention for each position is normalized using the softmax function.",
    "The formula illustrates that the attention score matrix can be derived by executing a dot product operation between the query and key, followed by division with a scaling factor of √ d k. Subsequently, the attention weights for each position are obtained by performing a softmax operation on the attention score matrix.",
    "The ultimate self-attention representation is achieved by multiplying the attention weights with the value matrix.",
    "The compatibility function employed in this process is a scaled dot product, thus rendering the computation process efficient.",
    "Additionally, the linear transformation of the inputs introduces ample expressive power."
  ]
}